When Profeſſors are found thus to fail both in their Ingreſſe to, and Progreſſe▪ in Church-fellowſhip, 'tis no wonder at all, if their Egreſſe therefrom be anſwerable; namely, injurious and ſcandalous to Brethren within, and to Neighbours without, by their hatefull and horrible rejection of the heavenly Oracles, from being the Rule, Square, and Touchſtone of their language, lives, and actions. As ſtrong fences are made to reſtrain the extravagant wanderings of bruitiſh Annimals; ſo the Sacred Scriptures are appointed to curb and bridle the wild
and wanton wits and ſpirits of the unruly reaſonable creatures. When the Children of diſobedience make bold to tread theſe fences down, who knows where or when they will ſtay or ſtand? When violent Torrents bear away and break down the withſtanding banks and dammes, who can tell at what time or place they will make a ſtoppe? When ſpiritual Paſſengers venture to ſpread the ſailes of their affections to the wind of their own wills, canne they expect to Anchor any where this ſide the brink of the bottomeleſſe pit? For the preventing of the Shipwrack, of whoſe Faith and good Conſcience, and for the further provoking of praying Perſons, to Petition that God would perſwade Japhet to dwell in the Tents of Shem; and cauſe the two ſticks of Joſeph and Judah, to become one in the hand of David our King; that they (ſpeaking a pure language, and leading a pious life) may be in a capacity to ſerve the Lord with own ſhoulder, and own conſent;
is his aimes in theſe endeavoures, who would be among thoſe few that follow the Lord fully; and is
